<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-24T10:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-24T10:29:00-05:00" n="237" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/772</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-24T19:00:00+03:31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 28, 6
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1660. Answering confidential circular August 18, received 21st.<note n="1" xml:id="d237fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_165">p.
                                    165</ref>.</note> Minister for Foreign Affairs says French and
                                Italian Ambassadors favor no reply to the Pope’s note, British
                                Ambassador disagrees but considers haste unnecessary. Russia feels
                                no reference to her in note is excuse for no reply, but one probably
                                will be made after conferring with Allies, and if so, Minister for
                                Foreign Affairs thinks that will be firmly negative.</p>
                            <closer>[<signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">Francis</persName></signed>]</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>